Step 1: Create new directory 
  mkdir myapp
  cd myapp/
Step 2:Create a new file 
  touch index.html
Step 3:Create a file name Dockerfile 
Step 4:Open the Dockerfile in a vim editor and add the following lines 
  FROM nginx
  COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html
(Important Steps):
Step 5:Start docker & build docker image from dockerfile 
  docker build -t myapp .
Step 6:update a user 
  sudo usermod -aG docker $USER
Step 7:Run docker conatiner from the images 
  docker run -p 8080:80 myapp
next 
  docker rub -d -p 8080:80 myapp
Step 8:Put the command for to see a IP adress
  ifconfig 
Step 9: Copy a ip and paste and access in a http://localhost6020:80
  Open a web browser and navigate to http://localhost :80 to see the "Hello World" meassage displayed in your web browser
  
